@startuml
title Read Path And Retrieval Modes

actor User
participant Runtime
participant "Read-Time Retrieval Planner" as Planner
participant "Answer Composer" as Composer
database DB

User -> Runtime: Ask memory-dependent question
Runtime -> Planner: plan_retrieval(request,\nrecent_context, core blocks)
Planner --> Runtime: answer_mode + retrieval budget

alt factual
    Runtime -> DB: load claims + tasks\n(+ evidence fallback if needed)
else rationale
    Runtime -> DB: load notes first\n+ claims + evidence fallback
else task
    Runtime -> DB: load active tasks\n+ supporting notes if needed
else mixed
    Runtime -> DB: load claims + notes + tasks
end

opt conflict or quote requested
    Runtime -> DB: load raw source evidence
end

DB --> Runtime: retrieval pack
Runtime -> Composer: compose_answer(request,\nretrieval pack, uncertainty flags)
Composer --> Runtime: grounded answer
Runtime --> User: final answer

note over Planner
Retrieval is bounded.
Budgets differ for factual, rationale, task, and mixed modes.
end note

note over Composer
Do not present notes as hard facts
without qualification.
end note

@enduml
